            <title>[HIVE-28338] Client connection count is not correct in HiveMetaStore#close</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-28338</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-24349&quot; title=&quot;Client connection count is not printed correctly in HiveMetastoreClient&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HIVE-24349&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HIVE-24349&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduced a bug in &lt;tt&gt;HiveMetaStoreClient&lt;/tt&gt; for embedded metastore, where the log would print negative connection counts.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Root Cause&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Connection count is only used in remote metastore, we do not need decrease connection counts when transport is null.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
